    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "3. Image Compression and Decompression using PCA."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ccIMrj7fwawr"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "nTbIr6VtkHOf"
      },
      "execution_count": 33,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "1. Load and Prepare Data:\n",
        "\n",
        "• Fetch an image of you choice.{If colour convert to grayscale}\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "N86syMMrwfUN"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "from PIL import Image\n",
        "\n",
        "image = Image.open(\"/content/drive/MyDrive/Ai and machine learning/images (1).jpg\").convert(\"L\")\n",
        "\n",
        "image_array = np.array(image)\n",
        "\n",
        "height, width = image_array.shape\n",
        "\n",
        "data = image_array.reshape(height, width)\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.imshow(image_array, cmap=\"gray\")\n",
        "plt.title(\"Original Image\")\n",
        "plt.axis(\"off\")\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 337
        },
        "id": "rDVXRC3uwkhI",
        "outputId": "d455adfa-b008-4a23-ee5d-3eef13cb9633"
      },
      "execution_count": 34,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
            ],
            "image/png": "\n"
          },
          "metadata": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "\n",
        "• Center the dataset - Standaridze the Data.\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "bAzP3Od4wuSo"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "mean = np.mean(data, axis=0)\n",
        "centered_data = data - mean"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "nJ5TQ1jbwv0w"
      },
      "execution_count": 35,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "• Calculate the covaraince matrix of the Standaridze data."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "CwN2GzXdxtMU"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "cov_matrix = np.cov(centered_data, rowvar=False)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Covariance Matrix Shape:\", cov_matrix.shape)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "_hNqFxQ_xyth",
        "outputId": "e91ead23-00af-4479-af0c-abbcedf9834a"
      },
      "execution_count": 36,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Covariance Matrix Shape: (300, 300)\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "2. Eigen Decomposition and Identifying Principal Components:\n",
        "\n",
        "• Compute Eigen Values and Eigen Vectors.\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "9wDmWTtox44Q"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "eigenvalues, eigenvectors = np.linalg.eigh(cov_matrix)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Eigenvalues Shape:\", eigenvalues.shape)\n",
        "print(\"Eigenvectors Shape:\", eigenvectors.shape)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "frGeIqHGySwG",
        "outputId": "da6396a1-3cc8-4926-ee7b-e57369bcaf09"
      },
      "execution_count": 37,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Eigenvalues Shape: (300,)\n",
            "Eigenvectors Shape: (300, 300)\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "• Sort the eigenvalues in descending order and choose the top k eigenvectors corresponding to\n",
        "the highest eigenvalues."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "W25UbIXuzi2W"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "sorted_indices = np.argsort(eigenvalues)[::-1]\n",
        "\n",
        "eigenvalues = eigenvalues[sorted_indices]\n",
        "eigenvectors = eigenvectors[:, sorted_indices]\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "k = 50\n",
        "top_k_eigenvectors = eigenvectors[:, :k]\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Top k Eigenvectors Shape:\", top_k_eigenvectors.shape)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "h6NUAR8bzk8J",
        "outputId": "a52392dc-4814-4438-84d2-13dbbb4143d4"
      },
      "execution_count": 38,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Top k Eigenvectors Shape: (300, 50)\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Identify the Principal Components with the help of cumulative Sum plot."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "gWRlBZn5yY3f"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "explained_variance_ratio = eigenvalues / np.sum(eigenvalues)\n",
        "\n",
        "cumulative_variance = np.cumsum(explained_variance_ratio)\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.plot(cumulative_variance)\n",
        "plt.title(\"Cumulative Explained Variance\")\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"Number of Principal Components\")\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"Cumulative Explained Variance\")\n",
        "plt.grid(True)\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 472
        },
        "id": "GJ7P57ggzwsZ",
        "outputId": "6e90ecf4-5997-4e2e-ae6d-d3a6c7209cc5"
      },
      "execution_count": 39,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
            ],
            "image/png": "\n"
          },
          "metadata": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "3. Reconstruction and Experiment:\n",
        "\n",
        "• Reconstruction: Transform the original data by multiplying it with the selected eigenvec-\n",
        "tors(PCs) to obtain a lower-dimensional representation."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "i6cD0HgDz7_R"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "compressed_data = np.dot(centered_data, top_k_eigenvectors)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Compressed Data Shape:\", compressed_data.shape)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "HvKHsPh6z7wa",
        "outputId": "e43ee582-a32c-43c2-8e78-80698fc1703a"
      },
      "execution_count": 40,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Compressed Data Shape: (168, 50)\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "reconstructed_image = np.dot(compressed_data, top_k_eigenvectors.T) + mean\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Reconstructed Image Shape:\", reconstructed_image.shape)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "aBV4usrP0E_z",
        "outputId": "f5325775-626c-443b-f38f-1377c3cdb606"
      },
      "execution_count": 41,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Reconstructed Image Shape: (168, 300)\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
